entries.femaleVariant: Are you V?
Please, step in the vehicle.
Hello, V. I'm Jefferson Peralez.
You've already spoken with Elizabeth, my wife.
[Take shard] All right. Lemme see the scroll.
All right. See what I can do.
Excellent. We'd be happy with any find that would clarify things, alleviate lingering doubts.
The braindance – it has to be back where it belongs today. Or a lot of people will be in a lot of trouble.
[Get in] Thanks.
OK…
Nice to meet you, Mr. Peralez.
Well, as you're probably aware, Mayor Lucius Rhyne recently passed.
Hm, right again, Liz.
You see, my wife is a great judge of character. Said this would work.
Now I see why.
What's this job?
Nice to meet you.
Straight to the matter at hand, huh? Hmhm…
Could engage in some small talk first.
So – whaddaya got for me?
My time' valuable, so is yours.
I mean, guess we could chat about the weather or debate where they serve the best ramen…
entries.maleVariant: I mean, I guess we could chat up the weather or debate where they serve the best ramen.

entries.femaleVariant: My time's pretty valuable. Pretty sure yours is too.
All the same to me, but…
Hahahahaha... Fair enough. To business it is.
Mrs. Peralez.
Elizabeth?
True.
Far as I know, case is closed already.
Case is closed.
His death was no secret. The media missed something?
There was an attempt on his life days before his passing.
Far as I remember, someone tried to zero Rhyne a few days before his death.
It was all over the news.
It is. Of course the police wrote it off as natural causes. Rhyne passed at home due to a "cardioimplant malfunction."
The NCPD sees no link. They're saying it was a random cyberpsycho attack.
Pf, of course it was. Media feasted for weeks. Pieces like that are their lifeblood.
And claimin' the mayor died of natural causes…
What makes you think the cops got it wrong? Got any evidence?
Causes unrelated to the attack. It's in the official reports. Rhyne died at home due to a "cardioimplant malfunction."
We want to know how, why, whatever else is pertinent.
Right. Think they missed somethin'?
We have reason to believe they did, yes.
But we're left wondering about the cyberpsycho attack at City Hall a few days earlier.
What makes you think the cops got it wrong?
The police say it was completely unrelated.
This got anything to do with the upcoming election?
Peralez? The one running for mayor?
Peralez? The one running for mayor of Night City?
entries.maleVariant: Peralez? Heh... The one running for mayor of Night City?

entries.femaleVariant: The one.
So the one who was DA until recently but just vaulted into a seat on the city council.
I gather you now understand why discretion is of the utmost importance.
These suspicions of yours… wouldn't have anything to do with the upcoming election, would they?
'Course they would. If Lucius Rhyne was murdered, we want to know, need to know.
Shortly before Rhyne passed, he made cuts in the NCPD budget. Perhaps got on someone's bad side that way.
In any case, we have the cyberpsycho attack on a BD.
Our chief of security scanned it but didn't find anything out of the ordinary, so to speak... We need a braindance editor, a real one. It's raw footage.
If you agree to help, you can see it right now.
Where'd you get it?
Where'd you get the scroll?
Rhyne was making a public appearance. BD scrolling's standard procedure for events like that.
Following the attack, the NCPD impounded the footage as evidence.
We had to pull many strings to extract it.
Lemme look at it now, then.
Carter, let's go.
[Sit and wait]
